1
00:00:52,119 --> 00:00:54,020
Tom, wait up.

2
00:00:54,719 --> 00:00:57,300
I heard about Megan. You doing okay?

3
00:00:58,560 --> 00:01:00,559
Train's running in 10 minutes.

4
00:01:00,560 --> 00:01:02,839
That's the thing
about this messed-up disease.

5
00:01:02,840 --> 00:01:06,780
My mother-in-law, God rest her soul,
she was only 66.

6
00:01:07,039 --> 00:01:09,340
Megan's 42.

7
00:01:10,920 --> 00:01:12,478
It's about time, Hog Head.

8
00:01:12,479 --> 00:01:15,380
Car trouble. Sorry, Tom.

9
00:01:15,719 --> 00:01:17,199
What do I care?

10
00:01:17,200 --> 00:01:21,140
I got your train today.
It's all set with the boys upstairs.

11
00:01:22,239 --> 00:01:25,900
Take some time off.
We got you covered.

12
00:01:27,280 --> 00:01:29,220
I wanna work.

13
00:01:30,719 --> 00:01:32,700
Wait up, Tom.

14
00:01:33,480 --> 00:01:37,639
All right, I wanna tell you this
as a friend and not your boss, Tom.

15
00:01:37,640 --> 00:01:39,438
You're not dealing with this.

16
00:01:39,439 --> 00:01:42,780
I'm dealing with it, my way.

17
00:01:42,799 --> 00:01:45,438
All right.
I'll give you all the streaks you want...

18
00:01:45,439 --> 00:01:47,839
...but if you don't
spend time with her now...

19
00:01:47,840 --> 00:01:50,460
...you're gonna regret it
the rest of your life.

20
00:01:57,120 --> 00:01:59,100
Give him his orders.

21
00:02:01,280 --> 00:02:03,060
See you, Tom.

22
00:02:09,560 --> 00:02:11,860
How long do I have?

23
00:02:13,040 --> 00:02:14,559
I can't answer that.

24
00:02:14,560 --> 00:02:16,940
Well, give me your best bet.

25
00:02:17,000 --> 00:02:19,340
I won't hold you to it.

26
00:02:39,439 --> 00:02:43,500
- Are you all right, Megan?
- Oh, yeah. I'm fine.

27
00:03:04,520 --> 00:03:06,758
Hey, what's the date today?

28
00:03:06,759 --> 00:03:08,638
Tuesday, February 2nd.

29
00:03:08,639 --> 00:03:11,340
Tom, do you really think
you should be driving?

30
00:03:11,919 --> 00:03:14,500
Don't you start with me too.

31
00:03:19,919 --> 00:03:24,300
This is Stargazer Express.
We are setting up and running.

32
00:03:24,599 --> 00:03:26,638
Wanda, your favorite train is leaving.

33
00:03:26,639 --> 00:03:29,038
About time. Stargazer Express.

34
00:03:29,039 --> 00:03:32,718
Come on, baby. Don't give us
a hard time over five little minutes.

35
00:03:32,719 --> 00:03:34,359
Because you know you want me.

36
00:03:34,360 --> 00:03:37,140
Like I want hemorrhoids.
Over and out. Romeo.

37
00:03:38,159 --> 00:03:39,900
Over and out.

38
00:03:40,520 --> 00:03:43,180
- Romeo, huh?
- Yes, sir.

39
00:03:43,479 --> 00:03:46,420
Love on a train.
Man, there ain't nothing like it.

40
00:04:06,319 --> 00:04:08,900
So. what do think about trains now?

41
00:04:10,599 --> 00:04:12,980
I love trains.

42
00:04:14,120 --> 00:04:15,860
I love you.

43
00:04:16,439 --> 00:04:20,140
Tom? You done?

44
00:04:20,919 --> 00:04:22,700
Yeah, I'm done.

45
00:04:40,000 --> 00:04:43,260
Welcome to the Stargazer Express.

46
00:04:43,360 --> 00:04:47,078
We'll be taking you all the way to
Oakland. and from there. on to Seattle.

47
00:04:47,079 --> 00:04:50,900
So sit back, relax, and enjoy the ride.

48
00:05:05,120 --> 00:05:06,679
Why, hello, Davey.

49
00:05:06,680 --> 00:05:10,300
How's your poor mother, bless her,
on this lovely Tuesday morning?

50
00:05:10,519 --> 00:05:13,318
- She's okay.
- Up and around, is she?

51
00:05:13,319 --> 00:05:15,719
Not yet. But soon.

52
00:05:15,720 --> 00:05:18,838
You sure?
Better tell her to watch her step then...

53
00:05:18,839 --> 00:05:21,340
- ... all that drinking.
- Okay, later, Mrs. Brown.

54
00:05:32,360 --> 00:05:34,860
Breakfast is ready, Mom.

55
00:05:36,839 --> 00:05:39,660
Did you say your morning prayers?

56
00:05:41,600 --> 00:05:43,500
Eat your eggs before they get cold.

57
00:05:44,720 --> 00:05:46,359
No, sweetie, I don't want it.

58
00:05:46,360 --> 00:05:48,660
Mom, you have to eat something.

59
00:05:50,839 --> 00:05:52,758
Kneel, Davey.

60
00:05:52,759 --> 00:05:54,599
I said my prayers.

61
00:05:54,600 --> 00:05:57,420
Well, say them again, sweetie.

62
00:06:00,240 --> 00:06:04,060
O God, come to my aid.

63
00:06:04,399 --> 00:06:06,580
I can't hear you, sweetie.

64
00:06:07,160 --> 00:06:10,359
O Lord, make haste to help me.

65
00:06:10,360 --> 00:06:15,740
Glory be to the Father, and to the Son,
and to the Holy Spirit.

66
00:06:17,759 --> 00:06:19,900
Hallelujah.

67
00:06:20,199 --> 00:06:22,198
You know, it's after 10.

68
00:06:22,199 --> 00:06:24,878
You slept so hard,
I didn't wanna wake you.

69
00:06:24,879 --> 00:06:27,078
I feel stronger.

70
00:06:27,079 --> 00:06:31,100
I knew it. I told you you'd feel better.

71
00:06:32,839 --> 00:06:35,500
How long before the train gets here,
sweetie?

72
00:06:36,279 --> 00:06:37,620
Thirty minutes.

73
00:06:39,319 --> 00:06:40,999
We're gonna see the train?

74
00:06:41,000 --> 00:06:42,958
Yeah, Davey.

75
00:06:42,959 --> 00:06:44,540
You mean it?

76
00:06:48,199 --> 00:06:50,919
We don't have to,
if you're not feeling well.

77
00:06:50,920 --> 00:06:53,780
I'm fine, baby.

78
00:06:54,680 --> 00:06:56,860
Here, that's two for you...

79
00:06:58,079 --> 00:07:00,580
...and three for me.

80
00:07:01,600 --> 00:07:05,660
- What for?
- To make us happy, baby.

81
00:07:07,360 --> 00:07:09,740
To make us happy.

82
00:07:27,480 --> 00:07:30,159
Honey, can you get the phone,
please?

83
00:07:30,160 --> 00:07:32,260
I got it, Mom.

84
00:07:34,120 --> 00:07:35,278
Hello?

85
00:07:35,279 --> 00:07:37,999
Hi. this is the principal
at Eastside Elementary School.

86
00:07:38,000 --> 00:07:40,919
I'm calling because Davey
hasn't been in school.

87
00:07:40,920 --> 00:07:44,460
Well, you see, his mother died.

88
00:07:45,480 --> 00:07:49,599
Oh. I'm very sorry.
We weren't aware of that.

89
00:07:49,600 --> 00:07:53,518
Please let us know
when he'll be back. all right?

90
00:07:53,519 --> 00:07:55,780
Okay. Thank you.

91
00:07:58,879 --> 00:08:00,540
Are you still taking classes?

92
00:08:00,720 --> 00:08:03,500
- Yeah. Of course.
- Accounting 101?

93
00:08:04,720 --> 00:08:07,380
Intermediate Accounting 3.

94
00:08:08,399 --> 00:08:11,679
I'm telling you, Tom, if you were smart,
you'd be going too.

95
00:08:11,680 --> 00:08:15,380
Trains, I mean, I love it, man,
but it's a dying business.

96
00:08:31,920 --> 00:08:33,700
Mom.

97
00:08:33,959 --> 00:08:35,860
Are you okay?

98
00:08:36,120 --> 00:08:38,340
Yeah, I'm fine.

99
00:08:41,000 --> 00:08:43,220
We'll wait, Davey.

100
00:08:44,800 --> 00:08:48,798
- We'll wait until it comes, and then-
- Did you know the Stargazer Express...

101
00:08:48,799 --> 00:08:50,678
...goes all the way to Seattle?

102
00:08:50,679 --> 00:08:53,020
I love you, baby.

103
00:08:54,039 --> 00:08:57,260
- Cold today.
- I know.

104
00:08:58,799 --> 00:09:00,199
Good morning, passengers.

105
00:09:00,200 --> 00:09:02,820
We are approaching
beautiful Simi Valley...

106
00:09:02,840 --> 00:09:05,220
...right on time.

107
00:09:05,519 --> 00:09:08,340
O God, you are my God.

108
00:09:08,559 --> 00:09:10,119
I wait for you from the dawn.

109
00:09:10,120 --> 00:09:12,780
There's two engineers
on each passenger train.

110
00:09:12,919 --> 00:09:15,740
My body longs for you.

111
00:09:16,320 --> 00:09:18,758
Pray with me, baby.

112
00:09:18,759 --> 00:09:22,220
- But I already prayed.
- Pray with me, Davey.

113
00:09:23,559 --> 00:09:26,300
My lips will praise you...

114
00:09:26,840 --> 00:09:30,100
...for your mercy is better
than life itself.

115
00:09:32,879 --> 00:09:34,820
It's here.

116
00:09:38,679 --> 00:09:40,860
Wait, Mom, don't go, it's coming.

117
00:09:49,159 --> 00:09:51,319
Mom, what are you doing?

118
00:09:51,320 --> 00:09:53,140
Mom!

119
00:09:53,600 --> 00:09:56,038
It's time to rest now, baby.

120
00:09:56,039 --> 00:09:57,918
- Mom. Mom, wake up.
- Be brave, honey.

121
00:09:57,919 --> 00:09:59,700
It's gonna be over soon, baby.

122
00:09:59,879 --> 00:10:03,079
Mom! The train's gonna come!

123
00:10:03,080 --> 00:10:05,580
- Mom, wake up! What are you doing?
- It's okay.

124
00:10:09,039 --> 00:10:11,359
- Object on the tracks.
- What?

125
00:10:11,360 --> 00:10:13,038
Objects on tracks. Call it in.

126
00:10:13,039 --> 00:10:15,398
- Jesus Christ. Jesus Christ.
- Call it in!

127
00:10:15,399 --> 00:10:17,038
All right, I'm slowing down.

128
00:10:17,039 --> 00:10:19,439
This is Stargazer Express,
approaching Highway 6.

129
00:10:19,440 --> 00:10:22,119
We have an object on tracks.
repeat, object on tracks.

130
00:10:22,120 --> 00:10:23,620
Sixty-eight miles an hour.

131
00:10:24,159 --> 00:10:25,860
Mom!

132
00:10:29,200 --> 00:10:31,060
Mom!

133
00:10:32,080 --> 00:10:34,020
Wake up!

134
00:10:34,639 --> 00:10:36,300
Oh, my God.

135
00:10:36,639 --> 00:10:39,380
- What's the speed?
- Fifty-five miles an hour.

136
00:10:39,679 --> 00:10:41,999
Still too fast, man. We're still too fast.

137
00:10:42,000 --> 00:10:43,839
- We gotta stop this train, man.
- No!

138
00:10:43,840 --> 00:10:46,518
No, no, no!
You're not stopping the goddamn train!

139
00:10:46,519 --> 00:10:48,558
What are you talking about?
We gotta try!

140
00:10:48,559 --> 00:10:50,678
We can't.
We got too many cars on the turn.

141
00:10:50,679 --> 00:10:53,918
- We have to take the chance!
- Hands off! We're following procedure!

142
00:10:53,919 --> 00:10:57,860
- Screw procedure, Tom!
- There's nothing we can do about it now!

143
00:10:58,000 --> 00:10:59,439
There is nothing we can do!

144
00:10:59,440 --> 00:11:02,700
Help! Someone help me!

145
00:11:03,720 --> 00:11:05,500
What are you doing?

146
00:11:06,639 --> 00:11:08,940
Mom! Mom! Get out!

147
00:11:10,279 --> 00:11:12,300
Fifty miles per hour.

148
00:11:12,799 --> 00:11:14,479
- Oh, my God.
- Forty-eight.

149
00:11:14,480 --> 00:11:17,580
- All right, brace for impact.
- Oh, my God. Oh, my God.

150
00:11:18,639 --> 00:11:19,940
Mom!

151
00:11:44,240 --> 00:11:46,260
Perfect.

152
00:12:11,279 --> 00:12:12,940
Thanks.

153
00:12:13,799 --> 00:12:15,460
May I?

154
00:12:18,080 --> 00:12:20,140
The railroad.

155
00:12:20,799 --> 00:12:23,020
Are you a trainman?

156
00:12:25,320 --> 00:12:27,420
You ever been on one?

157
00:12:29,399 --> 00:12:34,780
I don't know
if I should kiss you or slap you.

158
00:12:35,600 --> 00:12:38,918
Repeat after me: I.

159
00:12:38,919 --> 00:12:41,038
- I.
- Would like.

160
00:12:41,039 --> 00:12:42,678
Would like.

161
00:12:42,679 --> 00:12:45,278
To take you out sometime.

162
00:12:45,279 --> 00:12:47,959
To take you out sometime.
You'd go out with me?

163
00:12:47,960 --> 00:12:51,839
Well, now that you've asked me
so nicely, why not?

164
00:12:51,840 --> 00:12:53,620
Hey, Megan.

165
00:13:01,519 --> 00:13:04,500
Whoa, whoa, what are you doing?

166
00:13:06,320 --> 00:13:08,918
- What's going on?
- Okay.

167
00:13:08,919 --> 00:13:10,878
- Jesus.
- I'm...

168
00:13:10,879 --> 00:13:13,278
I'm planting flowers.

169
00:13:13,279 --> 00:13:16,199
Well, not in your condition.
You can't do this kind of work.

170
00:13:16,200 --> 00:13:18,959
Where's Tom? Oh, jeez. Hold on.

171
00:13:18,960 --> 00:13:20,599
Okay, thanks.

172
00:13:20,600 --> 00:13:23,119
I thought he was keeping
an eye on you.

173
00:13:23,120 --> 00:13:27,900
Sometimes I think he can't stand
to be around me.

174
00:13:30,159 --> 00:13:33,980
Here.
Just in case you change your mind.

175
00:13:38,360 --> 00:13:40,660
It's beautiful, isn't it?

176
00:13:41,039 --> 00:13:42,940
The piano?

177
00:13:43,879 --> 00:13:47,678
- I ordered it.
- You're kidding me.

178
00:13:47,679 --> 00:13:49,398
Oh, Megan.

179
00:13:49,399 --> 00:13:52,878
I'm gonna learn how to play.
I've always wanted to learn.

180
00:13:52,879 --> 00:13:55,260
Megan, you have to rest.

181
00:13:56,360 --> 00:14:02,620
Do not go gentle into that good night.
Rage. rage. rage

182
00:14:04,320 --> 00:14:07,599
Against the dying of the light.

183
00:14:07,600 --> 00:14:11,060
Is that what you're doing? Raging?

184
00:14:13,320 --> 00:14:17,620
It's a poem.
It's a Dylan Thomas poem.

185
00:14:19,919 --> 00:14:23,540
- Do you want me to get that?
- Yeah. Thanks.

186
00:14:30,159 --> 00:14:32,140
Stark residence.

187
00:14:32,559 --> 00:14:36,700
No, no. It's not.
Who should I say is calling?

188
00:14:39,840 --> 00:14:42,140
Oh, is he all right?

189
00:14:43,240 --> 00:14:44,620
Yes.

190
00:14:45,879 --> 00:14:49,060
Yes. Thank you.

191
00:14:50,559 --> 00:14:53,100
Tom had an accident.

192
00:15:06,279 --> 00:15:09,239
Give your specimen samples
to this officer.

193
00:15:09,240 --> 00:15:12,580
Cheers. Let me know if I'm pregnant.

194
00:15:19,399 --> 00:15:21,959
Visual clearance coming
off the corner was 300 feet.

195
00:15:21,960 --> 00:15:26,300
If you do the math, the posted was 60,
figure it was between 50 and 45, but...

196
00:15:28,200 --> 00:15:30,460
It was a suicide.

197
00:15:30,480 --> 00:15:33,398
No doubt about it.
We did everything by the book.

198
00:15:33,399 --> 00:15:35,918
- The box will tell you that.
- We know you did, Tom.

199
00:15:35,919 --> 00:15:38,260
It's just a complicated situation.

200
00:15:39,320 --> 00:15:42,439
It's a suicide. It's not complicated.

201
00:15:42,440 --> 00:15:44,999
Not when there's a woman
and a young child involved.

202
00:15:45,000 --> 00:15:46,798
We're bringing you on the carpet.

203
00:15:46,799 --> 00:15:50,479
Some whack-job
drives a car in front of my train...

204
00:15:50,480 --> 00:15:53,518
- ... and it's my fault?
- We don't have a choice on this one.

205
00:15:53,519 --> 00:15:56,558
No one remembers Victor Lopez,
but everybody knows Susan Smith.

206
00:15:56,559 --> 00:15:59,398
- What the hell's that supposed to mean?
- Victor Lopez.

207
00:15:59,399 --> 00:16:02,420
It's the homeless man
who dove under my train in Oxnard.

208
00:16:02,879 --> 00:16:05,918
Tom, nobody cares if some wacko
throws himself under a train...

209
00:16:05,919 --> 00:16:08,940
...but everybody feels
for a mother and her child.

210
00:16:10,080 --> 00:16:12,959
Wait, Tom, look.
Look, I'll talk to him. Hold up, Tom.

211
00:16:12,960 --> 00:16:14,999
Hey, it's a week, 10 days max,
you know?

212
00:16:15,000 --> 00:16:16,758
Take time off. Give us a chance...

213
00:16:16,759 --> 00:16:19,599
- ... to prove you did everything right.
- You know we did.

214
00:16:19,600 --> 00:16:22,060
You know this is a formality, Tom.

215
00:16:22,639 --> 00:16:24,860
We gotta do this.

216
00:16:25,639 --> 00:16:28,239
I'm sorry, excuse me.
This way, this way. Excuse me.

217
00:16:28,240 --> 00:16:30,060
You didn't stop.

218
00:16:30,360 --> 00:16:32,140
You didn't stop.

219
00:16:35,759 --> 00:16:37,678
Hi. Are you okay?

220
00:16:37,679 --> 00:16:39,839
- Yeah, I'm all right.
- What happened?

221
00:16:39,840 --> 00:16:41,918
Taking some time off.

222
00:16:41,919 --> 00:16:45,220
- They're making you?
- You saw the doctor?

223
00:16:47,559 --> 00:16:50,300
- Susan brought some soup over.
- Not hungry.

224
00:16:50,559 --> 00:16:53,020
You have to do chemo again?

225
00:16:54,399 --> 00:16:57,820
You know, this room, the kitchen?

226
00:16:58,799 --> 00:17:01,780
It's my favorite room
in the whole house.

227
00:17:02,080 --> 00:17:03,719
The only room we fully unpacked.

228
00:17:03,720 --> 00:17:06,940
Yeah. What did the doctor say, Meg?
What are the options?

229
00:17:07,639 --> 00:17:09,839
We don't have any options.

230
00:17:09,840 --> 00:17:13,820
I have days, weeks, maybe months.

231
00:17:16,519 --> 00:17:19,420
The cancer has metastasized
to my bones.

232
00:17:21,839 --> 00:17:24,479
So we'll treat it again.
It's gonna be hard, but-

233
00:17:24,480 --> 00:17:26,260
It's over.

234
00:17:27,000 --> 00:17:30,558
What are you talking about?
No, no, no. We gotta fight this. We-

235
00:17:30,559 --> 00:17:33,078
I'm done fighting, Tom.

236
00:17:33,079 --> 00:17:37,358
The chemo made me sick,
and the cancer's too advanced.

237
00:17:37,359 --> 00:17:40,318
I don't wanna spend the rest of my life
in a hospital room...

238
00:17:40,319 --> 00:17:42,719
...full of tubes and syringes
and oncologists.

239
00:17:42,720 --> 00:17:46,060
- Come on, there's gotta be something.
- There's nothing.

240
00:17:46,160 --> 00:17:49,838
We have to. We gotta try.
I mean, we gotta try to...

241
00:17:49,839 --> 00:17:53,358
Gotta try to find a way to deal,
you know, with-

242
00:17:53,359 --> 00:17:55,220
Death.

243
00:17:56,839 --> 00:17:58,500
Say it.

244
00:18:18,720 --> 00:18:22,919
You know what, this is only for tonight.
Tomorrow, we'll find you a good home.

245
00:18:22,920 --> 00:18:26,540
Okay? You don't feel tired?

246
00:18:27,559 --> 00:18:31,100
You need to get a little bit of sleep
if you can.

247
00:18:32,799 --> 00:18:34,940
Good night, David.

248
00:18:36,759 --> 00:18:38,420
Okay.

249
00:18:57,359 --> 00:19:01,159
Well, maybe now that you have
some time off...

250
00:19:01,160 --> 00:19:04,220
...maybe we can go to San Francisco.

251
00:19:06,359 --> 00:19:10,340
There's gonna be a hearing.
I have to be around to find out when.

252
00:19:11,759 --> 00:19:13,358
Great.

253
00:19:13,359 --> 00:19:15,919
An official excuse.

254
00:19:15,920 --> 00:19:18,700
No, it's not an excuse.

255
00:19:18,920 --> 00:19:21,780
If I'm absent at the hearing,
I'll lose my job.

256
00:19:23,200 --> 00:19:25,740
You're like sand, Tom.

257
00:19:25,920 --> 00:19:30,260
Harder I try to hold onto you,
the faster you slip through my fingers.

258
00:20:23,440 --> 00:20:25,220
Okay.

259
00:20:27,200 --> 00:20:29,180
It's okay.

260
00:20:35,640 --> 00:20:37,260
No.

261
00:20:41,599 --> 00:20:43,300
Out.

262
00:20:56,000 --> 00:20:57,740
Meggie?

263
00:21:11,839 --> 00:21:14,358
Tom thinks that we can help you.

264
00:21:14,359 --> 00:21:17,020
He was very convincing
over the phone.

265
00:21:17,200 --> 00:21:19,838
Well, we're a center
for alternative approaches...

266
00:21:19,839 --> 00:21:22,159
...to treat or ameliorate disease.

267
00:21:22,160 --> 00:21:28,220
We offer applied kinesiology,
cupping, even electromagnetic therapy.

268
00:21:28,680 --> 00:21:30,798
Can you cure me?

269
00:21:30,799 --> 00:21:35,580
As a professional in the medical field,
you know that there are no guarantees.

270
00:21:36,000 --> 00:21:40,060
However, we can try
to rejuvenate your system...

271
00:21:40,359 --> 00:21:43,758
...teach you a number
of relaxation techniques...

272
00:21:43,759 --> 00:21:47,278
...such as meditation,
deep breathing, self-hypnosis.

273
00:21:47,279 --> 00:21:50,100
All of these will help you relax.

274
00:21:50,319 --> 00:21:52,479
I don't wanna relax.

275
00:21:52,480 --> 00:21:54,358
- I wanna live.
- Honey...

276
00:21:54,359 --> 00:21:56,479
Why don't we just
hear what she has to say.

277
00:21:56,480 --> 00:22:00,159
It's all right, Tom.
Of course you wanna live, Megan.

278
00:22:00,160 --> 00:22:03,038
And I would like to spend
what little is left of my life...

279
00:22:03,039 --> 00:22:04,919
...doing exactly what I want to do...

280
00:22:04,920 --> 00:22:08,780
...which does not include
electromagnetic therapy.

281
00:22:11,519 --> 00:22:14,180
Okay. Thank you.

282
00:22:17,759 --> 00:22:20,318
- You're not even listening to me.
- What do you want?

283
00:22:20,319 --> 00:22:22,879
- What would you like me to do?
- What happened to us?

284
00:22:22,880 --> 00:22:24,999
- What are you talking about?
- You heard me.

285
00:22:25,000 --> 00:22:26,838
- Meggie, come on.
- Don't "Meggie" me.

286
00:22:26,839 --> 00:22:29,159
- I'm not some fragile thing.
- What do you want?

287
00:22:29,160 --> 00:22:31,919
I wanna know why
we never had children. How about that?

288
00:22:31,920 --> 00:22:35,479
I don't know, because we never found
the time. We never found the time.

289
00:22:35,480 --> 00:22:36,719
How could we have time?

290
00:22:36,720 --> 00:22:39,439
We moved in 10 different houses
in 15 years of marriage.

291
00:22:39,440 --> 00:22:41,679
I'm a trainman.
That's what trainmen do.

292
00:22:41,680 --> 00:22:44,118
That is not what trainmen do,
that's what you did.

293
00:22:44,119 --> 00:22:47,879
That's not what trainmen do.
It's not the rules for trainmen.

294
00:22:47,880 --> 00:22:52,380
How could anybody, anybody,
have a child like that?

295
00:22:52,400 --> 00:22:54,460
You got sick.

296
00:22:58,279 --> 00:23:00,860
You're blaming me?

297
00:23:04,759 --> 00:23:07,180
No, I'm not blaming anyone.

298
00:23:07,559 --> 00:23:10,060
It was just the way things worked out.

299
00:23:27,160 --> 00:23:32,020
I thought I had all this time...

300
00:23:32,559 --> 00:23:36,300
...to be a woman.

301
00:23:37,680 --> 00:23:39,220
To be a wife...

302
00:23:39,960 --> 00:23:44,420
...and a nurse, and a mother.

303
00:23:44,440 --> 00:23:49,038
Then I found out I didn't. I just didn't.

304
00:23:49,039 --> 00:23:51,260
I don't have any time.

305
00:23:53,119 --> 00:23:56,460
I probably would have made
a lousy father, anyway.

306
00:23:57,200 --> 00:24:00,100
I'm not afraid to die.

307
00:24:00,839 --> 00:24:04,820
But to think that I haven't lived?

308
00:24:08,119 --> 00:24:10,540
That terrifies me.

309
00:24:12,839 --> 00:24:15,719
Thank you so much
for agreeing to do this so quickly.

310
00:24:15,720 --> 00:24:17,798
You will be gentle with him,
though, Judy?

311
00:24:17,799 --> 00:24:20,220
I think he suffers from PTSD.

312
00:24:20,680 --> 00:24:22,460
These kids don't need pity.

313
00:24:22,519 --> 00:24:25,558
They require structure and discipline.
That's my gift to them.

314
00:24:25,559 --> 00:24:29,038
- Right, it's just that his mother was-
- Now, stop. You already told me.

315
00:24:29,039 --> 00:24:33,479
Separate yourself from your job, Renee.
They're not your children.

316
00:24:33,480 --> 00:24:36,380
Of course. You're right.

317
00:24:37,759 --> 00:24:39,420
Thanks.

318
00:24:45,039 --> 00:24:47,580
It's a nice room, huh?

319
00:24:50,160 --> 00:24:54,518
Well, it's a little pink, but at least
you have it all to yourself, right?

320
00:24:54,519 --> 00:24:57,740
It's definitely better
than temporary boarding.

321
00:24:59,720 --> 00:25:02,140
I don't wanna stay here.

322
00:25:02,640 --> 00:25:04,879
This is gonna be a great place for you,
David.

323
00:25:04,880 --> 00:25:07,318
Please don't make me stay.

324
00:25:07,319 --> 00:25:09,479
- You're gonna be safe.
- Please.

325
00:25:09,480 --> 00:25:12,558
Honey, you'll be safe,
and I think you'll really like Judy.

326
00:25:12,559 --> 00:25:17,820
You let her know if you need anything,
and she'll get in touch with me, all right?

327
00:25:21,519 --> 00:25:22,940
Bye.

328
00:25:42,599 --> 00:25:45,180
Used to be my girl's room.

329
00:25:46,759 --> 00:25:49,140
We asked for a girl...

330
00:25:49,839 --> 00:25:51,740
...but you were an emergency.

331
00:25:53,000 --> 00:25:55,460
You want some clean clothes?

332
00:26:03,079 --> 00:26:05,020
This'll have to do for now.

333
00:26:11,279 --> 00:26:13,460
We'll talk later.

334
00:26:15,599 --> 00:26:19,118
And it cleans for months.
Never scrub your toilet again.

335
00:26:19,119 --> 00:26:22,118
Authorities have just revealed
the identity of the woman...

336
00:26:22,119 --> 00:26:26,879
...that was killed in the Simi Valley
train crash as 27-year-old Laura Danner.

337
00:26:26,880 --> 00:26:29,598
The police say that her 11-year-old son.
David Danner...

338
00:26:29,599 --> 00:26:31,358
...had been with her in the car...

339
00:26:31,359 --> 00:26:35,118
...but he somehow managed
to escape the accident unharmed.

340
00:26:35,119 --> 00:26:39,278
I'm told that the senior engineer
who was driving that train. Tom Stark...

341
00:26:39,279 --> 00:26:43,118
...and his partner. Otis Higgs.
have been suspended pending-

342
00:26:43,119 --> 00:26:45,679
Kitchen is off-limits
between mealtimes.

343
00:26:45,680 --> 00:26:48,838
TV privileges are permission only.
Understood?

344
00:26:48,839 --> 00:26:50,838
- Yes.
- "Yes, ma'am. "

345
00:26:50,839 --> 00:26:53,780
As long as you live here,
you'll play by my rules.

346
00:26:54,400 --> 00:26:56,278
Listen to your own rules.

347
00:26:56,279 --> 00:26:58,060
Go to your room.

348
00:26:58,160 --> 00:27:00,780
You're the one
who should stay out of the kitchen.

349
00:27:01,200 --> 00:27:03,679
You're bad.
I knew it the moment I saw you.

350
00:27:03,680 --> 00:27:06,239
Get to your room. Now.

351
00:27:06,240 --> 00:27:07,900
Go.

352
00:27:11,200 --> 00:27:14,060
Get dressed and go to sleep.

353
00:28:24,079 --> 00:28:25,820
Hello?

354
00:28:30,519 --> 00:28:34,300
Hello? Anybody here?

355
00:28:43,279 --> 00:28:45,380
I fancy they're long gone.

356
00:28:46,599 --> 00:28:49,500
The officers.
They collected their evidence and left.

357
00:28:50,039 --> 00:28:51,479
You knew them?

358
00:28:51,480 --> 00:28:55,020
Laura and Davey? I suppose so.

359
00:28:58,119 --> 00:29:00,639
You look a bit pale, dearie.

360
00:29:00,640 --> 00:29:04,180
- I do feel a little...
- Come on. Let me get you a cup of tea.

361
00:29:05,839 --> 00:29:08,798
Tom? Where are you?

362
00:29:08,799 --> 00:29:10,740
I'm out in the garage.

363
00:29:11,519 --> 00:29:15,460
Hey, man, I'm sorry to disturb you
at the house, but...

364
00:29:19,279 --> 00:29:22,140
I had no idea you were
into model trains. This is nice.

365
00:29:23,720 --> 00:29:26,460
Hey, man, you mind
if we go get a beer or something?

366
00:29:27,359 --> 00:29:29,100
Yeah, sure.

367
00:29:30,480 --> 00:29:32,380
Let me get my coat.

368
00:29:36,559 --> 00:29:38,239
We'll let it brew a while.

369
00:29:38,240 --> 00:29:40,700
- You're very kind.
- Now...

370
00:29:40,759 --> 00:29:43,078
...I've lived in this building five years.

371
00:29:43,079 --> 00:29:45,598
Now, Laura and I,
we were never bosom buddies...

372
00:29:45,599 --> 00:29:48,399
...but you don't live
that long next door to someone...

373
00:29:48,400 --> 00:29:50,959
...without getting to know
them on an intimate level.

374
00:29:50,960 --> 00:29:53,460
So did she ever mention suicide
to you?

375
00:29:53,799 --> 00:29:55,919
Oh, you are a nosy one.

376
00:29:55,920 --> 00:29:57,719
Poking and snooping.

377
00:29:57,720 --> 00:29:59,798
Now, how did you find us?
Who sent you?

378
00:29:59,799 --> 00:30:01,999
- It's listed in...
- Well, dear, dear, dear.

379
00:30:02,000 --> 00:30:05,358
- Call information if you don't believe me.
- Trying times indeed, huh?

380
00:30:05,359 --> 00:30:07,100
Oh, cookies!

381
00:30:08,240 --> 00:30:09,980
No, thank you.

382
00:30:10,720 --> 00:30:12,260
Really.

383
00:30:13,119 --> 00:30:14,798
So you were saying, about Laura.

384
00:30:14,799 --> 00:30:17,439
Oh, yeah. Bless her.

385
00:30:17,440 --> 00:30:20,380
I looked after the boy
here and there, you know.

386
00:30:21,200 --> 00:30:25,798
Couldn't help but notice the men
coming and going from her apartment.

387
00:30:25,799 --> 00:30:27,798
I mean,
haven't been anybody for ages.

388
00:30:27,799 --> 00:30:30,358
But they used to flock
around her like hungry birds.

389
00:30:30,359 --> 00:30:32,118
But they stopped coming?

390
00:30:32,119 --> 00:30:34,159
Well, she had a breakdown.

391
00:30:34,160 --> 00:30:35,959
Nerves disease.

392
00:30:35,960 --> 00:30:39,180
Monstrous, really,
the tricks our mind plays on us.

393
00:30:39,680 --> 00:30:42,598
Well, I used to drop by, do chores.

394
00:30:42,599 --> 00:30:43,959
Cook for the boy.

395
00:30:43,960 --> 00:30:47,439
But frankly,
she needed professional help.

396
00:30:47,440 --> 00:30:49,340
Tea?

397
00:30:50,640 --> 00:30:52,540
So she gave up.

398
00:30:53,839 --> 00:30:56,220
Is that why you think she did it?

399
00:30:56,440 --> 00:30:58,060
I really don't know.

400
00:31:00,799 --> 00:31:03,420
- Have you thought about it?
- About what?

401
00:31:03,720 --> 00:31:05,420
The accident.

402
00:31:05,440 --> 00:31:07,758
I'm just...

403
00:31:07,759 --> 00:31:10,300
I'm having a little bit
of a hard time with it.

404
00:31:11,160 --> 00:31:14,318
Yeah, I- I don't wanna talk about it.

405
00:31:14,319 --> 00:31:18,180
Look, I'm- I'm gonna talk to N.B.

406
00:31:19,240 --> 00:31:21,300
I'm gonna give him my notice.

407
00:31:21,720 --> 00:31:25,439
No, you- You can't do that. That makes
it look like we did something wrong.

408
00:31:25,440 --> 00:31:27,838
- That's because we did.
- We didn't have a choice.

409
00:31:27,839 --> 00:31:30,199
- We didn't?
- No.

410
00:31:30,200 --> 00:31:32,038
If we'd used that emergency brake...

411
00:31:32,039 --> 00:31:34,679
...wheels could've flattened,
train could've derailed.

412
00:31:34,680 --> 00:31:36,838
- We'll never know-
- We're not gonna know...

413
00:31:36,839 --> 00:31:39,999
...but- But it was a judgment call,
and I- I made it.

414
00:31:40,000 --> 00:31:41,980
We killed a human being.

415
00:31:42,880 --> 00:31:44,740
A person, Tom. I don't know...

416
00:31:45,079 --> 00:31:46,740
...how I can...

417
00:31:47,920 --> 00:31:49,820
It was a suicide.

418
00:31:53,839 --> 00:31:55,740
Suicide.

419
00:31:58,119 --> 00:32:01,518
You know, the homeless man
was my first one? Victor Lopez?

420
00:32:01,519 --> 00:32:04,580
Come on, come on.
Can we talk about something else?

421
00:32:04,839 --> 00:32:07,660
It was right before
the end of the run and...

422
00:32:07,920 --> 00:32:11,100
I mean, we had a smooth ride
going for like 10 hours.

423
00:32:11,920 --> 00:32:16,919
And then I see him. I mean, he's
standing on the tracks, clear as day.

424
00:32:16,920 --> 00:32:18,558
And I'm blowing the horn. I'm-

425
00:32:18,559 --> 00:32:21,420
I'm ringing the bell.
I mean, I'm doing everything.

426
00:32:22,799 --> 00:32:25,020
He just ignored us.

427
00:32:25,400 --> 00:32:28,140
They turn us into executioners.

428
00:32:28,880 --> 00:32:31,260
You know what he did
right before we hit him?

429
00:32:33,000 --> 00:32:34,740
He smiled at us.

430
00:32:38,799 --> 00:32:42,060
He had a death wish, you know?

431
00:32:42,799 --> 00:32:44,780
Some people do.

432
00:32:46,240 --> 00:32:49,180
Other people don't wanna die,
they die anyway.

433
00:32:50,960 --> 00:32:53,220
I'm gonna wait
till the hearing's done...

434
00:32:54,039 --> 00:32:56,078
...but I'm giving my notice.

435
00:32:56,079 --> 00:32:57,639
Yeah, fine. Go ahead, do that.

436
00:32:57,640 --> 00:33:01,159
- Come on, man. Don't be an asshole.
- Because I got no time for a quitter.

437
00:33:01,160 --> 00:33:03,220
You know what your problem is?

438
00:33:04,119 --> 00:33:08,020
Everything is dying around you and you
just can't deal with it, can you?

439
00:33:08,319 --> 00:33:10,479
Hey! Hey, get out!

440
00:33:10,480 --> 00:33:13,199
Get out! Now! Let's go!

441
00:33:13,200 --> 00:33:15,060
Get out!

442
00:33:21,680 --> 00:33:23,999
Talk about my wife again, I'll kill you.

443
00:33:24,000 --> 00:33:26,758
You know what? Fuck you, Tom!
At least I'm alive.

444
00:33:26,759 --> 00:33:29,460
You're dead inside
and everybody knows it!

445
00:33:43,839 --> 00:33:45,340
What are you doing?

446
00:33:49,039 --> 00:33:53,838
I'm leaving for San Francisco,
tomorrow, alone.

447
00:33:53,839 --> 00:33:57,078
No, just wait...

448
00:33:57,079 --> 00:34:00,679
...wait until after the hearing
and I'll come with you.

449
00:34:00,680 --> 00:34:02,380
No, you won't.

450
00:34:03,359 --> 00:34:06,740
You'll- You'll sign up
for more train trips.

451
00:34:07,200 --> 00:34:09,660
Come on, Meg,
let me make it up to you.

452
00:34:12,559 --> 00:34:14,260
What for?

453
00:34:15,400 --> 00:34:17,580
A final goodbye?

454
00:34:28,000 --> 00:34:29,940
Good night.

455
00:35:28,800 --> 00:35:31,118
- Are you the conductor?
- Yes.

456
00:35:31,119 --> 00:35:33,518
I'm looking for my Uncle Tom.

457
00:35:33,519 --> 00:35:36,319
Yeah, I've seen him in this cab.
This is his train.

458
00:35:36,320 --> 00:35:39,820
You mean Tom Stark?
I didn't know he had relatives.

459
00:35:39,880 --> 00:35:42,140
Yeah. He has a sister.

460
00:35:42,800 --> 00:35:47,100
Sorry, kid, but Tom's not on duty today.
He's off because of the accident.

461
00:35:47,800 --> 00:35:51,919
Well, actually, I don't think
I have the right address.

462
00:35:51,920 --> 00:35:54,260
You want me to check his address?

463
00:35:54,280 --> 00:35:57,340
Could you hurry?
My mom's waiting in the car.

464
00:35:58,760 --> 00:36:00,839
You're bossy.

465
00:36:00,840 --> 00:36:03,340
You're just like your uncle.

466
00:36:03,360 --> 00:36:05,260
I'll just wait right here.

467
00:36:06,719 --> 00:36:08,940
Are you ready to say you're sorry?

468
00:37:03,559 --> 00:37:05,300
What happened?

469
00:37:07,480 --> 00:37:09,180
Don't go.

470
00:37:13,519 --> 00:37:15,500
I have to.

471
00:37:18,719 --> 00:37:21,900
What's gonna happen if you get worse?
I mean...

472
00:37:22,199 --> 00:37:27,620
...who's-?
Who's gonna take care of you there?

473
00:37:28,960 --> 00:37:31,060
I'll figure it out.

474
00:37:36,559 --> 00:37:38,540
Please don't go.

475
00:37:38,719 --> 00:37:41,340
Please. I'm sorry.

476
00:37:41,679 --> 00:37:43,540
Please.

477
00:38:03,159 --> 00:38:05,678
Okay, I'll notify the police, Judy.

478
00:38:05,679 --> 00:38:07,260
Thanks.

479
00:38:10,280 --> 00:38:12,220
Crap.

480
00:38:26,320 --> 00:38:28,540
I can't do this.

481
00:38:28,880 --> 00:38:31,980
It's too late, Tom. Come on.

482
00:38:41,679 --> 00:38:43,380
- You didn't stop!
- Hey!

483
00:38:43,440 --> 00:38:44,759
- Hey!
- What?

484
00:38:44,760 --> 00:38:47,158
- What are you doing? Hey!
- Stop! All right, stop.

485
00:38:47,159 --> 00:38:48,980
Get off me, kid.

486
00:38:49,159 --> 00:38:50,780
He killed my mom!

487
00:38:51,920 --> 00:38:54,158
Tom! Don't hurt him!

488
00:38:54,159 --> 00:38:55,558
- What are you, nuts?
- Stop!

489
00:38:55,559 --> 00:38:57,919
I didn't kill your mother,
she killed herself!

490
00:38:57,920 --> 00:38:59,919
- Will you stop it!
- No, she didn't!

491
00:38:59,920 --> 00:39:03,198
How fast were you going?
Sixty? Seventy?

492
00:39:03,199 --> 00:39:06,198
- I was going 48.
- You didn't even try to stop!

493
00:39:06,199 --> 00:39:07,839
I don't owe you an explanation!

494
00:39:07,840 --> 00:39:10,678
- Hey, Tom, stop it. Sweetie.
- Yes, you do!

495
00:39:10,679 --> 00:39:13,759
- Stop it!
- You could've stopped! You didn't try!

496
00:39:13,760 --> 00:39:15,919
- You didn't even try!
- Listen, come on.

497
00:39:15,920 --> 00:39:17,238
Okay, come on.

498
00:39:17,239 --> 00:39:20,158
- He killed my mother.
- Your mother killed herself.

499
00:39:20,159 --> 00:39:22,860
Come sit down. Let's have some water.
Come on.

500
00:39:29,280 --> 00:39:31,118
- It doesn't say.
- Yes, it does.

501
00:39:31,119 --> 00:39:33,020
Show him where.

502
00:39:33,039 --> 00:39:36,420
